<item>
            <title>[SOLR-11586] Restored collection uses stateFormat=1 instead of 2</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11586</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11560&quot; title=&quot;RestoreCmd resolves incorrect property from DocCollection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-11560&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-11560&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I noticed that the restored collection is using stateFormat=1 . It should be creating the collection with stateFormat=2 which would mean the collection should be residing under &lt;tt&gt;&quot;/collections/collection_name/state.json&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13113415">SOLR-11586</key>
            <summary>Restored collection uses stateFormat=1 instead of 2</summary>
