                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16227436" author="varunthacker" created="Tue, 31 Oct 2017 20:11:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=noble.paul&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;noble.paul&quot;&gt;noble.paul&lt;/a&gt; if no stateFormat param is provided , the create collection code explicitly sets stateFormat to 2 . The restore API code wasn&apos;t doing this so the restored collection was getting created in /clusterstate.json . Should we change the default behaviour to use stateFormat=2 if the param is not provided? Offcourse it needs to be another Jira but any reason for not dong so?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
